---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Upstart Podcast Case Study | Dino Favara Jr."
  description="One concept. 24K views. A clear channel outlier. Went from 1-2K view clips to a 12-24x outperformer through clip selection and editing systems."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <!-- Back link -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-10">
      <a href="/work" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-primary/70 hover:text-primary transition-colors duration-200">
        &larr; All case studies
      </a>
    </section>

    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-8 pb-12">
      <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-mint/20 text-dark/70 tracking-wide mb-6">
        Podcast Clips
      </span>
      <h1 class="font-display text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,3.2rem)] leading-[1.1] tracking-tight text-dark mb-4">
        Upstart Podcast Shorts
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg font-light text-dark/60 leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        One concept. 24K views. A 12-24x outperformer on a channel averaging 1-2K views per clip.
      </p>

      <!-- Service tags -->
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-6">
        {['Podcast Clip Strategy', 'Clip Selection', 'Short-Form Editing', 'YouTube Shorts', 'Outlier Development'].map(tag => (
          <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-dark/10 bg-white/60 text-xs font-medium text-dark/55">
            {tag}
          </span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Before / After -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-12">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-dark/8 bg-white/70 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[1fr_auto_1fr]">
          <!-- Before -->
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-10 px-8 text-center">
            <span class="text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-dark/40 mb-3">Avg Views Before</span>
            <span class="font-display text-[2.8rem] leading-none text-red-500">1-2K</span>
            <span class="mt-2 text-sm font-light text-dark/50">per clip</span>
          </div>
          <!-- Arrow -->
          <div class="hidden md:flex items-center justify-center px-4">
            <span class="text-2xl text-dark/20">&rarr;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex md:hidden items-center justify-center py-2">
            <span class="text-2xl text-dark/20">&darr;</span>
          </div>
          <!-- After -->
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-10 px-8 text-center bg-mint/8">
            <span class="text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-dark/40 mb-3">Outlier Views</span>
            <span class="font-display text-[2.8rem] leading-none text-dark">24K</span>
            <span class="mt-2 text-sm font-light text-dark/50">on one clip</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Metrics Grid -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-12">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
        {[
          { value: '24K', label: 'Outlier Views', sub: '(single clip)' },
          { value: '12-24x', label: 'Outperformance', sub: '(vs. channel avg)' },
          { value: '1', label: 'Concept', sub: '(strategically built)' },
          { value: '↑', label: 'Channel Benchmark', sub: '(new ceiling set)' },
        ].map(m => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-dark/8 bg-white/60 p-5 text-center">
            <span class="font-display text-2xl text-dark">{m.value}</span>
            <p class="mt-1 text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-dark/45">{m.label}</p>
            <p class="mt-0.5 text-[10px] text-dark/35">{m.sub}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Body Content -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-16">
      <article class="prose-custom">
        <h3>The Situation</h3>
        <p>Upstart Podcast was producing short-form clips from their long-form episodes but seeing minimal traction. Most clips averaged 1-2K views — enough to feel like it was working, not enough to actually grow. The problem wasn't the podcast. It was the clip selection and concept architecture. They were clipping what was easy, not what would travel.</p>

        <h3>The Approach</h3>
        <p>Podcast clip strategy is deceptively hard. Most teams pull the most quotable moment and hit publish. But <strong>what spreads on short-form isn't the best quote — it's the moment with the most tension, surprise, or emotional resolution.</strong></p>
        <p>I audited their existing clips, identified the pattern behind their best performers, and built a clip selection framework around that. Then I developed one concept specifically architected to outperform: the right topic, the right moment in the episode, the right hook structure, and the right editing rhythm to hold attention to the end.</p>

        <h3>The Results</h3>
        <p>That clip hit 24K views — a 12-24x outperformer on their channel. More importantly, it established a proof of concept: their content could break out if the selection and structure were right. The framework that built that clip became the foundation for their ongoing strategy.</p>
        <p>Podcast teams often underestimate their short-form potential because they're measuring the wrong thing. Views on a clip aren't about how good the podcast is. They're about how well the clip was chosen and built. Change the system, change the results.</p>
      </article>

      <!-- Timeline -->
      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-dark/8">
        <span class="text-sm font-light text-dark/45">Result: single concept</span>
        <div class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-full rounded-full bg-dark/6 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="h-full rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-mint to-periwinkle" style="width: 100%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Back to Work CTA -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-20">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-dark/8 bg-white/60 p-8 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-xl text-dark">Want results like this?</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-light text-dark/55 mt-1">Let's talk about building your content engine.</p>
        </div>
        <a
          href="mailto:dino@mercurysocialmedia.com"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-7 py-3.5 rounded-full bg-primary text-off-white font-medium text-sm hover:bg-primary/90 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-primary/40 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-200 active:scale-95 whitespace-nowrap"
        >
          Email me &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-custom h3 {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--dark);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .prose-custom h3:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .prose-custom p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(26, 21, 35, 0.65);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .prose-custom strong {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--dark);
  }
  .prose-custom blockquote {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--primary);
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    background: rgba(107, 92, 231, 0.04);
    border-radius: 0 0.75rem 0.75rem 0;
  }
  .prose-custom blockquote p {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prose-custom blockquote cite {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: rgba(26, 21, 35, 0.45);
  }
</style>
